        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 10:05PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1005 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Goodnight, or 7 miles southeast of Claude, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
